      <title>Reminder - answers to my "10 questions" ?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Shaman&amp;message.id=1881#M1881</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It's now been over two weeks since Brenlo wrote:&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0066&gt;&lt;EM&gt;I forwarded the 10 questions along and am awaiting a response.&amp;nbsp; As soon as I have one I will post it.&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0066&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Brenlo&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0066&gt;&lt;EM&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0066&gt;&lt;EM&gt;Brenlo Bixiebopper&lt;BR&gt;Community Relations Manager&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Brenlo - Any update on when we might expect answers from the devs on my "10 questions"?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Copied here for your convenience.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #1:&amp;nbsp; Please explain in detail the reasoning behind the "100% / 64% / 47%" ratio for cleric/druid/shaman heals?&amp;nbsp; Also comment on whether this is expected to continue as is?&amp;nbsp; And why is this ratio not also applied to our 10-second "incomplete heal" spells as well?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #2:&amp;nbsp; Please explain the role you expect for shaman to fill in groups fighting mobs which mitigate slows, since the way slow mitigation was implemented decreases our already marginal advantage over other slowing classes?&amp;nbsp; Please explain how you expect shamans to carry out that role (perhaps an example which includes mana spent, time spent, damage mitigated, damage dealt, and so on, along with a situation where we are the best choice class to fill that role)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #3:&amp;nbsp; In a full raid of 72 people, one would expect there to be 4-5 shamans, assuming classes are in balance and about equally represented.&amp;nbsp; What is your vision of what shamans #3, #4, and #5 should be doing on a raid?&amp;nbsp; How is shaman #3-#5 better than having cleric #6,#7,#8 or wizard #6,#7,#8?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #4:&amp;nbsp; If a group already has sufficient healing and a slower, but invites a shaman nevertheless, how much worse is that shaman's target DPS than say adding a wizard?&amp;nbsp; magician?&amp;nbsp; beastlord?&amp;nbsp; paladin?&amp;nbsp; necro?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #5:&amp;nbsp; If stat buffs are supposed to actually do something, please explain to us what going from 250 to 350 in each stat is supposed to do and under what conditions stat buffs should actually be used?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #6:&amp;nbsp; Please tell us why DoTs have gone from being more efficient and yielding more damage than the best nukes in the game&amp;nbsp;to their present state of less damage, more agro, less efficiency, and fights that don't last for their entire duration?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #7:&amp;nbsp; Please tell us under exactly what conditions rabid bear is supposed to be useful?&amp;nbsp; And why its extreme power indicates a base reuse time of 2+ hours.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #8:&amp;nbsp; Please tell us who most of our alchemy made potions are supposed to be used by and under what conditions?&amp;nbsp; The please justify the current prices.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #9:&amp;nbsp; Please tell us why malos has such a large cast/recast&amp;nbsp;tiime, since given that almost none of our spells have innate resist adjustments we're clearly expected to cast it on most mobs before casting damage spells.&amp;nbsp; Most other classes have damage spells with innate resist modifiers, even if they have damage spells with resist adjustments.&amp;nbsp; (See druids with -50 on their much more efficient rain spell&amp;nbsp;despite having a cold debuf spell&amp;nbsp;as an example.)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#33cc00&gt;QUESTION #10:&amp;nbsp; Please explain why it would be a game altering change to allow shaman pets to have innate SoW?&amp;nbsp; Innate dual wield?&amp;nbsp; Or even why you don't just add an item that summons pet usable junk weapons so we can be spared the frustration of realizing we forgot to restock our backpack full of rusty daggers before crawling all the way to some out of the way GoD zone?&amp;nbsp; While you're at it, explain where our pets are supposed to be in the DPS and surviveability hierarchies of the other pet classes?&amp;nbsp; Are our pets supposed to lose to lower level SK pets?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;A final note to other shamans:&amp;nbsp; please don't post negative stuff on this reminder thread.&amp;nbsp; I'd prefer for the questions to actually be answered.&amp;nbsp; I already know that most of you don't think they will be.&amp;nbsp; No need to post it here :)&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
